BT 0 g /F2 18 Tf 232.56 740 Td (UNDERSTANDING BPD) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 730 m 540 730 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 700 Td (Borderline Personality Disorder is characterized by:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 675 Td (- Intense and unstable emotions that change rapidly) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 655 Td (- Fear of abandonment \(real or imagined\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 635 Td (- Unstable relationships \(idealization/devaluation\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 615 Td (- Unstable sense of self/identity) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 595 Td (- Impulsive behaviors \(spending, substances, risky behavior\)) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 575 Td (- Chronic feelings of emptiness) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 555 Td (- Intense anger that is hard to control) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 535 Td (- Dissociation under stress) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 90 515 Td (- Self-harm or suicidal thoughts) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 480 Td (IMPORTANT: BPD is NOT a life sentence. With skills training \(like DBT\),) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 462 Td (many people achieve significant recovery.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
